      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "URBAN TIGER (4) isn't a quick beginner but comes home hard, finishing out of the frame two back but did wind up strongly to place when second (22.60) in a Grade 5 at Maitland. Makes plenty of appeal. REDEEM A ARCADIA (2) stalked the lead from the inside draw then took over turning and burst clear to score (17.53) at this track in a Grade 5 over 300m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Can make it two on the bounce. BLACK KELLY (1) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing seventh (18.68) in a Grade 5 at this track. Likely to play a prominent role. LITTLE KAOS (8) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.",
